			<ns0:name>pho...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/117980525918552686609/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Currently Native Client only support threads.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
The process support will allow porting of wider range of existing POSIX-based applications and is prerequisite for implementing fork().

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Provide process support in micro-kernel style, where parent process is responsible for initialization of newly spawned child process.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
The untrusted code can spawn new process, load module and start its execution.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-09-28T15:26:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-09-07T03:50:42.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:state>open</ns2:state><ns0:title>Provide process support in Native Client</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Enhancement</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-All</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3019/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3019" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/3019" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>3</ns2:stars><ns2:id>3019</ns2:id></ns0:entry>